import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['US_Gross', 'Worldwide_Gross']]
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='US_Gross', y='Worldwide_Gross')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Production_Budget'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Production_Budget'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Production_Budget'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Production_Budget', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Production_Budget'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['MPAA_Rating', 'Major_Genre'])
    chart_data = data.groupby(['MPAA_Rating', 'Major_Genre']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='MPAA_Rating', y='count', hue='Major_Genre', data=chart_data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating and Major_Genre?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
